CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 5, 1965, pg. 6, reads: "The Twilighters Club - celebrated its 20th anniversary this year by entertaining their mothers, mothers-in-law, aunts and other relatives at a dinner recently. Held at Weinstein's Kennilworth Restaurant, Mrs. Eric Springer was guest speaker.  Left to right, seated: Mrs. Carolyn Kirkland, Mrs. Theodore Ford, president, and Mrs. Charlotte Grimes.  Standing: Mmes. Bobetta Johnson, Norma Grant, Ann Harris, Claudia Davis, Eleanor Burden, Vivian Colbert and Hattie Smith.  Missing from the picture are Mmes. Thelma Thompson, Kathryn Woodruff and Gloria Smith. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women in the Twilighters Club, seated from left: Carolyn Kirkland, Mrs. Theodore Ford, Charlotte Grimes; standing: Bobetta Johnson, Norma Grant, Ann Harris, Claudia Davis, Eleanor Burden, Vivian Colbert, and Hattie Smith, posed in Weinstein's Restaurant, in Kennilworth Building, East Liberty, another version
